 

'''Josephine Akosua Adomako Ampofo'''  y''ɛ'' Ghanani nhomsuamu ɔbenfo a  ɔkyer''ɛ'' ade fa bɔbiasu ho wɔ suapɔn a ''ɛ''ne University of Ghana<ref>Akosua Adomako Ampofo Bio (africanstudies.org)</ref><ref>Professor Akosua Adomako Ampofo | Institute of African Studies | University of Ghana (ug.edu.gh)</ref>. ɔy''ɛ'' obi a ɔko ma mma yiyedie,na afei nso, ɔpere ma nnipa yiyie die<ref>Prof. Akosua Adomako Ampofo – Professor of African and Gender studies – Ghana – Young African Women Congress (yawcafrica.org)</ref>.

== Ne mmofrase ne nhomasua ==
Ampofo maame y''ɛ'' Germanini na ne papa y''ɛ'' Ghanani a ofiri Asanteman mu. Ne papa abusua no y''ɛ'' nea wɔdɔm amanykuo a ''ɛ''de Converntions Peoples Party (CPP). Ampofo kɔɔ ntoaso sukuu a ''ɛ''ne Aburi Girl's Secondary school. Ampofo nyaa suapɔn abɔdin krataa a edikan firi sapɔn a ''ɛ''de Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology, bre a owie n'adesua a ''ɛ''fa adansie ho nnema no. ɔtoa so suaa ade faa mpontuo nhyehyɛeɛ ho ma no nyaa abodin krataa a ''ɛ''ne Master Degree. Ampofo nyaa suapɔn abɔdin a ''ɛ''kɔ anim a ''ɛ''ne Phd fri suapɔn a ''ɛ''de Vanderbilt University bre a owiee n'adesua a ''ɛ''fa nnipa nney''ɛ''e ho no. ɔsan nso kura abɔdin krataa a ene Post-Graduate Diploma a onya firii suapɔn a ''ɛ''de Technical Universit of Dortmond, a ''ɛ''wɔ Germany.

== Nhomasua mu Adwuma ==
Ampofo hy''ɛ'' adekyere ase wo University of Ghana wo afe 1989. Wo afe 1994 ne 1995 ntam no, na okura dibea a ene Junior Fulbright. Wo afe 2005 mu no, obeyee obaa odikan se otitenani wo suapon no fa bi a ede Centre for Gender Studies and Advocacy (CEGENSA), okuraa saa dibea no kosii afe 2009 mu. Wo afe 2008 mu no, obeyee koowaa krataa mu samufoɔ kowaa krataa a ene Ghana Studies, na okuraa saa dibea no kosii afe 2013 mu. Osan nso yee adwuma se koowaa krataa mu samufoɔ  ma Contemporary Journal of African Studies.

Na oye Mellon Fellow wo afe 2014 mu wo University of Cape Coast Town, faako a oyee adwuma ma Centre for African Studies. Wo afe 2015 mu no, oyee adwuma se Senior Fulbright Scholar-in-Residence a ewo suapon a ene Concordia University Irvine. 

Oye adwuma se Kohunufo maa nwumakuo a emu bi ne [[:en:United_Nations_Development_Fund_for_Women|UNIFEM]], [[:en:UNICEF|UNICEF]], [[:en:World_Health_Organization|World Health Organization (WHO)]], [[:en:Save_the_Children|Save the Children]], [[:en:Joint_United_Nations_Programme_on_HIV/AIDS|UNAIDS]], [[:en:Ministry_of_Women_and_Children's_Affairs|Ministry for Gender & Social Protection, Ghana]]; Participatory Development Associates; Gender Studies and Human Rights Documentation Centre and [[:en:Kofi_Annan_International_Peacekeeping_Training_Centre|Kofi Annan International Peacekeeping Training Centre]].

== Adwumakuo a odom ==
Wo afe 2019 mu no, se okandifo ma African Studies Association of Africa (ASAA) no, ohwe maa woye nyiamu a edikan wo East Africa. Ampofo ka won a wohyehyee  ekuo a ede ASAA a wohyehyei wo afe 2013 mu no. Osan nso dom akuo ahorow a ede Association and Sociologists for Women and Society, (SWS), [[:en:African_Studies_Association|African Studies Association]], United States, Ghana Domestic Violence Coalition, the Network for Women's Rights in Ghana, the Council for Social Science Research in Africa (CODESRIA)  ne[[:en:International_Sociological_Association|International Sociological Association, (ISA)]]. osan nso dom ekuo a ede [[:en:Ghana_Academy_of_Arts_and_Sciences|Ghana Academy of Arts and Sciences]]
